.SH NAME
polyglot\-scenarios \- repo\-owned executable scenario proving slices
.SH PURPOSE
This page explains the first executable scenarios shipped in the
repository.
.SH WHEN TO USE
Read this page when you want a runnable pattern that ties runtime
guidance, task execution, evidence artifacts, and verification together.
.SH PRIMARY COMMANDS
.IP
.EX
task scenarios:python\-maintenance
task scenarios:java\-maintenance
task scenarios:verify
.EE
.SH WORKFLOW
The current scenario slice stays deliberately small.
.PP
It uses two repo\-owned maintenance examples:
.IP \(bu 2
Python dependency maintenance with the \f[CR]uv\-lock\f[R] strategy
.IP \(bu 2
Java dependency maintenance with the Gradle\-first update path
.PP
Each scenario:
.IP "1." 3
runs through existing task commands in the proving workspace
.IP "2." 3
checks the expected evidence and report artifacts
.IP "3." 3
writes a scenario result artifact under \f[CR].artifacts/scenarios/\f[R]
.PP
The scenarios are thin wrappers over the existing task contract.
.PP
They are not a new workflow system.
